## Field research findings (20 goactivebooking sites audited)

### Template groups
- A+B (simple/single-location): 45% of businesses. 1-10 products, minimal categories.
- C (multi-location): 20%. Location selector needed, standardized products per location.
- D (complex/multi-category): 35%. Memberships + events + booking + PT + klippekort. Needs flexible category system.
- 3 templates cover 100% of use cases.

### Visual quality
- 90% scored 1-2 out of 5. Every site uses the same BRP Angular SPA with zero layout customization.
- Only customization available: logo + primary color. This is the core problem we solve.

### Product types (by frequency)
- Memberships/subscriptions: 80%
- Group classes: 70%
- Klippekort/punch cards: 40%
- Events/courses: 35%
- Personal training: 25%
- Court/facility booking: 20%
- Gift cards: 15%

### Signup flow (standard across 95% of sites)
- CPR/personnummer is the primary identifier (70%). Must support CPR lookup in addition to email.
- "Register without CPR" option exists as a toggle to manual form.
- Standard fields (95%+): first name, last name, DOB, address, postal, city, phone (with country code), country dropdown.
- Email is inferred/hidden behind CPR flow in most cases.
- Gender: varies, some require, some skip.
- No custom fields or emergency contacts observed in any signup.
- Customer type selector is universal: Voksen/Almindelig always present, Student/Senior/Pensionist vary.

### Payment
- Always BRP-managed (DIBS/NETS card or autogiro). We never handle payment processing.
- MobilePay mentioned but rare.

### Geography
- Sweden: 55%, Denmark: 25%, Norway: 20%.
- Multi-language support (DA + SV + NO) needed. BRP API handles translations via Accept-Language header. We handle UI strings.
- Language mismatch is common: BRP UI chrome shows in Danish even on SE/NO sites. We can fix this.

### Campaigns
- ~40% of sites have highlighted campaign/intro offers. Coupon support matters.

### Technical observations
- All sites expose document.goactivebooking config JSON with categories, settings, business units.
- Same cookie banner (CookieInformation) across all sites.
- BRP UI is 100% standardized Angular SPA. No variation in flow or layout.

### Implications for build
- CPR/personnummer lookup must be a first-class signup flow, not just email.
- Customer type selector (Voksen, Student, Senior) must be built into checkout.
- Support at minimum DA, SV, NO for UI strings.
- Campaign/featured product highlighting is a real need (40% of sites use it).
- Court/facility booking and group class scheduling are v2 features, not MVP.